element.name: Can't see the wood for the trees by Wackihunters, Traditional Cache (1/1)
element.description: Should be an easy one and will hopefully provide you with a nice walk. Main obstacle is that signal sometimes weakens in the woods.
element.long-description: Go first to car park in Balrath Wood N53 37.061 W006 30.462 and set out from there. Plastic container with selection of bric a brac. Please hide well as although quiet their are a number of children spend that spend a lot of time playing in this wood. There is a group called the Balrath Woods Preservation Group that look to promote the appreciation of the environmental and social value of our woodlands and to protect this important part of our natural heritage for the future. You can find out more at http://balrathwoods.com/html/home1.html The wood has a variety of walks (short and long) as well as a nature trail with numbered posts. For more info see http://www.meath.ie/latest_news/balrath.html
element.encoded-hints: The five "Foreign" ladies have her, but no it's not five
element.url-name: Can't see the wood for the trees
